content: I am sorry. I will behave.
Todays topic is my game from WC against Vladimir Sushkov and some of my memories about the rounds and tournament
I was 3rd in the tournament table
I didn't think about place or anything at that time
first rounds I just played and then found myself from the top 3
Didn't you dream of the champion at that time? :P
That's why you can get it, maybe :)
It didn't even come to my mind :)
I had a lot of luck
that I had to play against in last 4 rounds
were Ando Sushkov Sinyov and Yamaguchi
In the tournament my main weapon was D11
if i can earn 0.5 from 4 players is good reasult for me :))))
I opened it 5 times from 6 of my games
that I had to set opening
Not that I had liked D11 so very much than other openings
but I felt myself quite confidently there
last round D8 was an exeption, against Yamaguchi
before the last round, in the evening we discussed with Ants
and we thought I have good chances to get at least a draw in D8 with both colours
at the same time there was a game Ando-Synov going on
I had expected his next move
but the 14th move was a big suprise
<GrandMaster> but the 14th move was a big suprise
i need to see it in database, i cannot guess the suprise move, sorry
Before the game I had had a little study about 14-K8
but no way I thought about J7
He and Chingin had analyzed it against me
Anyway, I fell into a deep thinking period
The time control was 120 minutes per player
and after that bayomi 30 moves in 30 minutes
After the game I remembered that I had seen
It was Artemev, who showed me his game against Klimashin in same position
But I ignored those analyzes in my plans during the game
so practically I didn't have experience with this move ;)
or is there more ways for black ?
Please tell what do you think...
white next move may put on L7
from Klimashin's in his game against Artemiev
Maybe better when white plays the four first
maybe somebody else wants to continue
if somebody has plan, can go first
We are trying to find defense against 21-f8 :)
Ando, you can go as black
k10 is important in such pattern
and if black takes it first
so as we did a little analyze
it showed that 15 isn't a winning idea
hard to say if its true :)
but its what our little analyze showed
24-i5 maybe better as defense, but white might lose vct threat by that,
then black can go freely up
i dont know if this is win or not
if yes, then next is h12
and then maybe easier to win
and I went on in positional style
I didn't think about something like I should get attack panically
I didn't think about the result at all
My tactic was just to play

mayhem, endlessroad, dittp, luwenzhe, yyfcsd, callings, AUTHOR, killer21st, Xespok, H8, SSHJ, sakura, slamduk, casar, sunrain, finite555, fallnavy, coco_yuang, yun_shou, weigui, LiuJianping, shuwang, Ando, scm2000, Aurora, ouyang, sosei, bawangwan, mestupid, virag, Intotherenju.
after using a lot of time with the 15th move
yeah these moves are very typical in this opening
I thouvht the position was going to look as it does
and now it was Sushkov's turn
He didn't chose a standard move
seems (and probably is) the most logical answer
The game would have been different if he had chosen that
my answer was in positional style
but theres a way of attacking in a straight style also
Now its time to think a bit
not, but more easily can develop black
Sushkov mentioned that black can get strong attack
but there was a mistake in moves sequence
what if we start with the three?
but if its win or not
and my time would be little
so I chose more easier way
now it seems quite balanced position
I was the one who chose the game's turn
Positional style is only black's weapon
there were 2 points in the game
where I could have chosen another plan
Much depends on the style if you can't tell which is better for sure
and I had to keep up the activity
were on the left down side
I think its very likely black will get draw at least
and more likely white would be the one to make the mistake
Which would be the next move you would move?
but Sushkov did his move quite quickly
and he chose the more passive one
and now 31 is quite dangouros already
and support to left side would be weaker
he fell into a deeper think
I don't know how to comment this move
then its much better for white for the future
but maybe he was a bit unsure
here I had my bayomi started
he had a lot of time left
maybe half hours till nayomi time
I saw that I can't win in this corner
so I played few logical, maybe tricky moves
lower left side is the side
where the last battle will take place
and I am going to move there first
but probably not enough recources to win
I wanted to get extra power
that I had at the upper side
and if I try it now
then where will white close it now ?
no need to defend at upper
Where is the next white's move ?
and he did it very quickly
here there is no white mistake, all white move lose :)
and where white has to close the three now ?
L11 J9 and h14 i14 f14
so he had to play the stone to upper side
and now I had the needed power, I think
then white can simply block the three from d
and after that I had maybe 7 minutes left
so I might have gotten nervous :)
I had to do a lot of moves
I thought which is better f5 or f4
these mistakes gave me the needed power to win
and that made the lower corner powerful
the mistakes wouldn't have been faithful maybe if these would have made 'lonely'
then maybe not would have won
and now I'll show you the end
if 42 at j12, there is now win in the right side?
in this point he used a lot of time also
so we both had few time
but there was nothing to do
so I thought I would play d6
Here it was the moment where his time ran out also, but there was also nothing to do...
After this came I became the leader
a key game and you won it
but the last 2 rounds were still there
and only after I had won the 10th round also
I began to think I might become the champion..
It wasn't in my plans - to become the champion
